PrecisOrder designed (a) to correct a number of errors in the description of the lands referred to in Order in Council P.C. 1989-2/2436 of December 7, 1989 (which authorized the NATIONAL CAPITAL COMMISSION and the Department of PUBLIC WORKS to carry out a series of land exchanges involving, among others, Jacques Cartier Park, Brewery Creek and the Canadian Museum of Civilization), and (b) to grant several new easements which will facilitate access to and administration of those properties.
